.TH BKEYS 1 "2026-06-29" "smartmet-monitor" "SmartMet Server"
.SH NAME
bkeys \- top API keys in a SmartMet access log
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bkeys
.RI [ \-n\  N ]
.RI [ \-s\  reqs|ms|mb|err ]
.RI [ LOG-FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bkeys
groups access\-log entries by API key (the last field of each log
line) and prints the top
.B N
keys sorted by the chosen metric. Each row shows request count,
mean latency, the 4xx and 5xx error rates, total bandwidth in MB,
and a horizontal bar scaled to the leading metric.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n \ N
Number of API keys to show. Default
.BR 20 .
.TP
.BI \-s \ SORT
Sort column. One of
.BR reqs ,\  ms ,\  mb ,\  err
(err = 4xx+5xx error count). Default
.BR reqs .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bstat (1),
.BR bchart (1),
.BR burls (1),
.BR bstatus (1),
.BR bwho (1),
.BR bip (1),
.BR smtop (1)
